{
  "stem": "13817.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "You couldn't have any maids anymore.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "The maids had to be at least 40 years old if she were to be a maid in a Jewish place or it had to be a Jewish girl.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "And this when really the harassment started.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "The doctors couldn't practice anymore.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] Excuse me.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "[DRINKS] The Jewish doctors couldn't practice anymore, the lawyers couldn't anymore.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "And only for Jewish people they could.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not-- not until-- real-- real pressure to start leave-- to leave came after '38 after the Kristallnacht.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But I had one uncle who lived in [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[INAUDIBLE] is the part of Germany what was separated from the main country by the corridor for the Polish-- for Poland which had-- which gave Poland a-- a road towards the ocean, to the-- to Danzig-- Gdansk the Poland called it-- to-- to have access to the sea.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he lived up in that part, and this part was very anti-Semitic and very Hitler.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he was already beaten in 1934.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They beat him up there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "When he came back to Kerpen where he was born, and he, his wife, and two children.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And he lived in Kerpen where-- like I said before, the anti-Semitists were there, but it wasn't that intense because all them people grew up there and everybody knew each other, like I said before.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So there were a certain amount of anti-Semitism.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was a certain amount of Nazis there, but they-- they weren't as-- as-- as brutal as they were over in [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he was then the first one-- he said when he-- in '37 when it got still started getting worse he said, I'm not gonna stay.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We're going to get out of here.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And he-- he left Germany.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
